MirOS base system and BSD - TOU
-------------------------------

This is /usr/share/doc/legal/LICENCE, available online at
http://cvs.mirbsd.de/src/share/doc/legal/ or any other
CVSweb-enabled mirror, such as cvsweb.allbsd.org in Japan.

This file contains the terms and conditions which MirOS base
and MirOS BSD are covered under.

The MirOS Project consists of a loosely bound group of deve-
lopers of which most are Europe-based, some in Canada or USA
and some other places of the world; these developers work on
MirOS together as "committers" (people with direct write ac-
cess to MirOS) and former committers (together, authors), as
well as "contributors" who submit patches or help otherwise.
MirBSD is defined as the content of the MirOS Project's lea-
der's /usr/src and /usr/ports directories; usually MirOS BSD
and MirPorts; thus, MirOS is derived from MirBSD™.

