The following persons are MirOS developers:
* Thorsten „mirabilos“ Glaser <tg@mirbsd.org>
* Dr. Benny „benz“ Siegert <bsiegert@gmx.de>

Some other MirOS developers have contributed to the website,
the MirPorts Framework, MirOS BSD or the other hosted and/or
contributed software.


For an overview of all other terms and conditions that cover
parts of MirOS, refer to the file 1stREAD in the current di-
rectory and the files it refers to.

The MirOS Project strives to make as much of our work as po-
ssible, as well as inherited work we redistribute, available
under OSD compliant licences (see www.opensource.org), where
OSI certification is not a requirement, due to braindead po-
licies of OSI.
We strongly request people to not reuse our work in material
covered by problematic licences such as the GNU FDL.

We ask all of our contributors to publish their work under a
licence boilerplate derived from the "licence.template" file
and request them to always use the disclaimer shown in this,
even if contributor is not bound by EU law.
We also ask all contributors to be: either at least 18 years
old, or at least 7 years old and have been given a parental,
generic permit to do business related to open source softwa-
re (or at least specific to MirOS), which enables them to be
fully contractually capable for this specific area of deals.
Contributor is responsible to provide the parental statement
in non-electronic form, giving this permission, if required,
and a proof of age, on request.


